name: Daniel Manzano
bio: Hugely grateful and honored to be 1/3 of Boyce Avenue

social_posts.post_text: You don’t know patience until you’ve coached 5-year-olds. Adorable though. Oceana had a really clutch basket in the championship game when the score was close and her face when she made it was priceless. Also kian is almost taller than me. 🙄 Another great season with @suncoastbasketballclub. Happy holidays everyone!
PHILIPPINES here’s looking at you! Last night in Manila was a great reminder of why we love playing here. xo 📷 @miciel.221
Having some fun in Cebu. It’s great to be back in the Philippines! xo 📷 @miciel.221

@miciel.221 is on this tour with us taking photos and video. I got emotional on stage the other night seeing him in the crowd. I started remembering how he was even there for our very first shows—just a little 6-month-old under the merch table in his infant carrier with his ear muffs on, while @shelly_manzano and @jetmanzano were selling merch. It’s been amazing having him here with us for this tour now that he’s a teenager, even if we can’t get him to take a normal photo 🙄😂 #nocap #ongod #w #sadboihoursclub #rizz
Davao! Thanks for an amazing Valentine’s! Philippines, we’ll miss you. Until next time! Up next, India. xo 📸 @miciel.221
The India shows were a vibe! 📷 @mustacherodeo & @miciel.221
We got to see our cousin @gbregon, meet his better half @jenamstarr, and celebrate @fabianmanzano’s bday all in one weekend.

Throwback to my first ever father-daughter dance. ❤️
Tour sarts tonight! Let’s get it Cardiff! ✊
Feeling fortunate to have Kian on tour with us. Feels like he was a little baby on tour just yesterday. Now he’s a teenager!
This UK / Ireland tour has been so so good. Thanks for keeping us inspired! ❤️

Had an awesome trip out to the English countryside to visit Charlie from @theluxurywatchcompany. We got to talk about building a YouTube channel, watch collecting, and more. Charlie is absolute class. Thanks for the gifts as well.
Big thanks to Jay at @salisburyabc for opening up the gym and training us. What a great gym and great people.
Hugely grateful and honored to be 1/3 of Boyce Avenue
